	(text "Out To PLC"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 254.508 26.162 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 5.08 5.08)
				(thickness 1.016)
				(bold yes)
			)
		)
		(uuid "063eef9e-cdd1-4485-9567-909e4e31e103")
	)
	(text_box "The architecture begins with the host ESP32 driving a CD74HC138 3-to-8 line decoder to control bus multiplexing. By manipulating three digital address lines, the ESP32 targets the active-low Chip Select (CS) inputs of individual bridge chips. In this design, we utilize six of the decoder's eight available outputs.\n\nEach output targets one of six SC16IS752 dual-channel UART-to-SPI bridge controllers. Because each bridge chip independently manages two hardware UART channels, this multiplexed network allows the single ESP32 SPI master to interface with twelve discrete LD2410C radar sensors.\n\nTelemetry gathered from the sensors is aggregated by the ESP32, formatted into network packets, and transmitted over the local Ethernet show network.\n\nNOTE: The original target of this board was to read 24 sensors on one board. To achieve 24 sensors, this board should be duplicated and ran in parallel. Adding 2 more SC16IS752 chips to this design increases the max theoretical capacity to 16 sensors, but requires a complete board redesign."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
